<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-04-0954 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the summer of 1976 the Danish Social Democratic Party tried to passthe nuclear power project, but had to withdraw the proposal because ofgrowing opposition in the party and the population. A line of technicalinvestigations were initiated but every time grounds for a decision werereached, new demands were made or demands for new investigations of thetechnical consequences of nuclear power. When the technical foundationfor a decision was ready in the autumn 1984 the social democrats finallyretreated for political reasons - and the conservative government hadno urge to promote a decision either. The convinced supporters of nuclearpower were politically isolated. (SM). 40 refs.</TEXT></DOC>